    "async-discipline": {
      "name": "async-discipline",
      "description": "INVESTIGATION RESULT: Almost all 36 items are false positives \u2014 the functions already await all their async work correctly. The linter flags them because the outer function signature says async but never uses a bare await at the top level (it awaits inside try/catch, conditionals, etc). The fix for ~33 of 36 items is: REMOVE THE ASYNC KEYWORD if the function returns a Promise directly, OR verify the function genuinely needs async. Only 3 items need ADD VOID (test file + migration effect).",
      "issue_ids": [
        "smells::src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/components/__tests__/submitSegmentTask.test.ts::async_no_await"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-03-04T04:48:40+00:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-04T13:31:58+00:00",
      "auto": false,
      "cluster_key": "",
      "action": "Read each function. Don't blanket void everything.",
      "user_modified": true,
      "action_steps": [
        "Focus: desloppify plan focus async-discipline",
        "For each item: read 10 lines around the flagged line",
        "Check: does the function body actually await anything? If yes, async is correct \u2014 the item is a false positive, resolve with note 'async is correct, all code paths await'",
        "If function returns a Promise directly without await, REMOVE ASYNC and let it return Promise naturally",
        "Exception: submitSegmentTask.test.ts lines 72 and 114 \u2014 add void wrapper",
        "Exception: useLoraCategoryMigration.ts line 30 \u2014 already uses void, verify and resolve",
        "Verify: npx tsc --noEmit after each batch of ~5 files",
        "Resolve each: desloppify plan resolve <id> --note <action taken> --confirm"
      ]
    },
