          "5. After: npx tsc --noEmit && npm run build && desloppify scan --path src/shared/components/PhaseConfigSelectorModal"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-04T04:52:23+00:00",
      "action": "cluster_update",
      "issue_ids": [],
      "cluster_name": "struct-shared-misc",
      "actor": "user",
      "note": null,
      "detail": {
        "description": "29 remaining structural items across shared components, hooks, and lib. These are individual decompositions \u2014 no cluster-level pattern. Work through one at a time. For each: read the file, identify 2-3 responsibility boundaries, extract.",
        "steps": [
          "1. Sort by LOC descending \u2014 biggest files first (individualTravelSegment 870, PromptGenerationControls 742, MediaGalleryItem 701, etc.)",
          "2. For each file: read it, identify what concerns are mixed (JSX + fetching + handlers = needs splitting)",
          "3. Pattern: extract hooks into a hooks/ subfolder, extract utilities into utils, keep the component as a thin shell",
          "4. DO NOT create a new abstraction layer. Just move code to where it belongs.",
          "5. If a file is 500-550 LOC and cleanly organized (one concern), consider leaving it with a note \u2014 not everything over 500 LOC is wrong",
          "6. After every 5 files: npx tsc --noEmit && desloppify scan --path ."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-04T04:52:34+00:00",
      "action": "cluster_update",
      "issue_ids": [],
      "cluster_name": "review-cross-module",
      "actor": "user",
      "note": null,
      "detail": {
        "description": "HIGHEST SCORE IMPACT. Cross-module arch is at 44% \u2014 worst dimension. 4 issues about import boundaries being violated. Fix these and the strict score moves the most.",
        "steps": [
          "1. Error runtime hub: the shared error runtime is imported into integration internals. Create a clear boundary \u2014 integration code should not reach into shared error internals. Move error types to a shared contract, keep runtime in app layer.",
          "2. Import cycle (ImageGenerationForm): already addressed in trivial-fixes cluster. Just verify it's resolved.",
          "3. Supabase client boundary erosion: audit where supabase client is imported directly. Create a domain access layer or repository pattern so components don't import supabase directly.",
          "4. Dynamic imports as cycle workarounds: find the dynamic imports, trace what cycle they're avoiding, fix the underlying cycle instead.",
          "5. After: desloppify scan --path . and check cross-module arch dimension score"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-04T04:52:44+00:00",
      "action": "cluster_update",
      "issue_ids": [],
      "cluster_name": "review-design-coherence",
      "actor": "user",
      "note": null,
      "detail": {
        "description": "2nd worst dimension at 46.9%. Auth is fragmented across multiple hooks/components. Async flows have race conditions. Upload feedback lies to the user.",
        "steps": [
          "1. Auth fragmentation (2 issues): map all auth-related hooks/components. Consolidate into a single auth lifecycle controller. useHomeAuth should not bundle OAuth + PWA + referral + auth listening.",
          "2. Clip manager async race: add AbortController or cleanup function to the duration hydration effect. When component unmounts or state changes, cancel pending work.",
          "3. Upload feedback: tie the progress UI state directly to the mutation's onSuccess/onError. Don't decouple feedback from outcome.",
          "4. Lightbox controller overaggregation: this gets addressed by struct-medialightbox decomposition. Just verify after that cluster is done.",
          "5. Supabase types god module: this is auto-generated \u2014 skip with justification if not already skipped.",
          "6. After: desloppify scan --path . and check design coherence dimension score"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-03-04T04:52:56+00:00",
      "action": "cluster_update",
      "issue_ids": [],
      "cluster_name": "review-api-init-error",
      "actor": "user",
      "note": null,
      "detail": {
        "description": "Three related dimensions: API coherence (48.5%), Init coupling (50.4%), Error consistency (58.2%). Cache keys are inconsistent, auth state leaks on signout, errors are swallowed.",
        "steps": [
          "1. Cache key unification (2 issues): find all query key definitions for generation-task mapping. Pick ONE pattern. Update all consumers. Test with React Query devtools that invalidation still works.",
          "2. Stale auth cache on signout: find the tool settings cache. Add a listener on auth state change that clears it. Test: sign out, sign in as different user, verify no stale data.",
          "3. Join clips localStorage queue: replace ambient localStorage queue with explicit state passing. The consumer should not depend on timing of when localStorage was written.",
          "4. Realtime singleton: make the connection lazy-initialized (not on import). Constructor should not have side effects.",
          "5. Optimistic update failure: when the optimistic update's mutation fails, roll back the optimistic state. Don't persist the optimistic value as truth.",
          "6. Task details error handling: when task details fetch fails, show an error state, not an empty state. Users need to know something went wrong.",
          "7. After: desloppify scan --path . and check all 3 dimension scores"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
