        "steps": [
          "1. Work through ONE AT A TIME. Read the full finding description (desloppify show <id>).",
          "2. For items that overlap with completed structural work: verify the decomposition addressed it, then resolve with a note.",
          "3. For items about dual API surfaces (project context, task details): pick the newer API, migrate consumers, deprecate the old one.",
          "4. For items about package organization (shared/hooks, shared/lib): move domain-specific code to src/domains/ or feature directories.",
          "5. For test strategy items: write the missing tests. Don't just note that tests are missing.",
          "6. For type safety items: add runtime validation (zod or manual checks) at the boundary where external data enters.",
          "7. DO NOT resolve items you haven't actually read and fixed. If you can't explain what you changed, you didn't fix it."
        ]
      }
    },
